latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This was meant to be a photograph, but now it's a video of @katrinakaif and me in front of a fan, our hair looking straight out of a shampoo ad (I'm standing on a stool, by the way, trying not to tumble)...

Actor and entrepreneur Katrina Kaif is @cosmoindia's covergirl this month, for the 25th Anniversary Issue, and during this covershoot, one of the first things I noticed was the actor's keen eye for every little detail...she was involved in the camera lighting, in how the photoshoot set looked, the way a lock of hair framed her face... 

It was later, during our interview, that I discovered some of the many layers that lie behind Katrina's immaculate (and somewhat unapproachable) exterior. This is a woman with remarkable drive, an incredible spirit, and a mind that is sharp and astute. And then, almost without warning, there is also a beautiful, compelling vulnerability that makes Katrina Kaif so likeable, you want to hug her.

Read the full interview in this month's issue of Cosmo India, where Katrina talks about her life, dreams, and her passions--namely, Bollywood, her incredibly successful beauty brand @kaybykatrina , and finding balance and joy. 

#CosmoIndiaTurns25

latestIgtvVideos.title: Can a Dryer Actually Make Your Hair HEALTHIER and MOISTURISED?!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Answer: Yes! I'm a blow-dry addict..and people have been telling me forever that I will suitably fry my hair. They're right, of course: all those years of heat exposure have left my fine hair even finer, with brittle ends.
.
So when @panasonic_india  asked me to test their new dryer—the Nanoe hairdryer—which promises to *add moisture to your hair* I said, 'Yes, please!'. Here's how it works: the dryer infuses hair strands with moisture-rich nanoe™ particles that penetrate into hair cuticles to maintain the moisture balance of hair as well as scalp. I have never been able to achieve a smooth blow-dry at home, but this dryer certainly added smoothness and took care of the frizz. Bonus: the Panasonic Nanoe dryer *also* moisturises and balances the scalp, which means your head is actually healthier after a blow-dry! (Hoorah for smart technology!)
.
The Panasonic Nanoe Dryer is available on Amazon.in, and is certainly a great example of breakthrough-technology in beauty...just in time for the festivities and the wedding season.
.
Check out the product online for more details, and also some of my favourite blow-dry tips, below:

MY BLOW-DRY HACKS:

 
* I like to blow-dry my hair when it's 70-80 percent dry, using a round brush. Curly-haired peeps might prefer to dry hair that's a little wetter
.

* I like to hold the brush in my dominant hand (right, for me) and the hairdryer in the other, for better styling control. The Panasonic Nanoe Dryer is very light, so you won't end up with aching arms.

 .
* A little heat-protectant goes a long way, in keeping ends looking smoother.

 .
* Your hair dryer must always be moving, or you'll place too much heat on one section.

 .
* If your hair is fine or thin, you don't need to blow-dry at the highest setting—medium will do.

 .

latestIgtvVideos.title: 6 Fabulous Products Worth Trying from Katrina's #KayBeauty Makeup Range
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I remember interviewing @katrinakaif during the launch of her makeup collection with @mynykaa . And I remember her being incredibly passionate about every single product...she had been very involved, the Nykaa team told me later, testing each formulation and shade over and over until she was satisfied.
Today, as #KayBeautyTurns1 (congratulations, #Katrina!) I'm pulling out my favourites. These are the #KayBeauty products I've used, loved, and will use again...

1) @kaybykatrina Matteinee Matte Lip Crayon in Entourage: look at the colour payoff on this gorgeous, vivid pink! This lipstick range does it for me because it lasts HOURS, but also feels weightless (matte lip lovers will be happy to know that it won't leave your lips with that sticky 'smacky' finish).

2) @kaybykatrina Matteinee Matte Lip Crayon in Countdown: all the benefits as  above, plus this shade is the kind of pinky-nude that works on every skin tone beautifully! 

3) @kaybykatrina EyeStylist Liquid Eyeliner: I envy girls with perfect winged liners. I'm rubbish at drawing them. But, after many years, I've learnt that the secret lies in the brush. This particular liner has a 'flexi tip' which offers enough grip to draw on your line with ease, but also flexibility to draw that elusive, delicate wing without stomping your feet in frustration.

4) @kaybykatrina ChiselStar Contour Stick:  a contour tool in a sleek stick is such an effortless idea! I'm wearing the shade Coco Focus, which is a little darker than what is recommended for me, but it blends so well that it works for evenings when I really want definition.

5) @kaybykatrina Metal Show Eyeshadow Stick in Special Effects: I'm not an eyeshadow pro...never have been. But I enjoy how quickly I can dab this on my lids, for a put-together metallic finish. This is a creme-to-matte formula, which is *incredibly* easy to blend.

6) @kaybykatrina Illuminating Highlighter: My idea of a good highliter is one that doesn't show little specks of glitter when you move, and therefore offers a subtler finish. This highliter, in the shade Champagne Fizz hits the right notes!
.
.

#kaybeautyturns1 #itskaytobeyou #makeupthatkares #india #indianbeauty

latestIgtvVideos.title: The Simple Trick That Cured My Acne
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My skin is fairly okay; I'd give it a 6-7 on 10 on most days. Until suddenly, for no good reason, it began breaking out. One day, I'd look into the mirror and feel really good about how everything looked. And the next day, I would find a cute little zit on my cheek. 
As anyone waking up to a breakout knows, it can be a real kill-joy. And the cycle of breakout-scar-breakout can be especially upsetting. 
This drove me nuts because I simply couldn't figure out why this was happening! This cycle continued for years, until I discovered the Korean art of double cleansing. 
I have often wished someone had told me about the double cleansing technique before...so here I am, sharing details, with the hope that this will help you with any random bouts of breakouts, too (especially if you wear makeup or have very oily skin). If you try it (or already do it), I'd love to hear about your experience! .
.
.
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Styling a Pink PowerSuit for Monday Morning
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
After weeks of living in my pyjamas, I decided it was time to break out of the monotony. As several studies prove, looking professional makes you *feel* professional...and even boosts productivity. What you wear doesn't just impact how others view you, it also has a bearing on how you feel about yourself. And so, a few days ago, I decided it was time to dress up for #WorkfromHome. Once again.
. 
I pulled  out my @marksandspencerindia pink powersuit and put up images on Insta Stories for your styling suggestions. I asked whether I should team this vivid pink with hoops or danglers; comfy slippers or elegant flats. Thank you to the thousands of you who voted...I styled myself based on your feedback and truly enjoyed the interactive, 'community feel' of it all.
.

So here is my look for today. A bubblegum pink powersuit from @marksandspencerindia that, to me, echoes how I would like to feel right now: bright and joyful. Dressing up gave me a sense of normalcy, in uncertain times. And, as I discovered, I miss the simple joy of deciding between two lipsticks to match my outfit with! .
#RethinkWithMandS
.

latestPosts.caption:
Last week, I flew out to London to experience The Newt in Somerset x Burberry summer takeover. 

Burberry badminton courts..
Croquet lawns trimmed in the Burberry check. 
Sunny walks in ancient gardens.
Delightful installations.
And my sari paired with a Burberry trenchcoat.

Across the estate’s 2,000 acres, every beautiful detail is an ode to countryside living, reimagined through the iconic lens of British fashion.

The experience of this special collaboration  felt like walking through a living moodboard as Burberry codes entwined with nature in modern yet elegant ways. 
A reminder that luxury, at its best, isn’t just worn; it’s felt. And luxury merged with the great outdoors is a very special experience,  indeed.

#BurberryAtTheNewt #TheNewtInSomerset #GreatBritishSummer #FashionInNature #TheWordMagazine #QuietLuxury #BurberrySummer2025

latestPosts.caption:
Coffee at the iconic United Coffee House in Connaught Place, Delhi, with this beautiful @burberry Highlands Bowling Bag.

Established in 1942, United Coffee House was originally formed as a gathering ground for intellectuals, artists, and beaurocrats. Dressed in chandeliers, buttered toast, and, of course, coffee, this establishment feels like nostalgia in the best way possible.

As for the Burberry Higglands Bowling Bag, this beauty makes for the perfect coffee date with its jacquard-woven fabric and a promise to go with pretty much any outfit you select. Love!

#Burberry

latestPosts.caption:
I didn't take enough pictures because I was so busy soaking in the magic of what 25 years of Indian fashion looks like: The people, the passion, the fashion. 

So here's what we have here:

1. Me, dressed in a @raw_mango dupatta, draped as a skirt. The loveliest @shivanbhatiya helped me drape this beauty.

2. The formidable trio behind Indian fashion: @sunilsethifdci , Chairman of FDCI; @sunandakhaitan , Lakme Innovations Lead; and @jaspreetchandol , Group Vice President,  Reliance Brands Limited.

3. Faces and people I ❤️. Always so lovely seeing you, @maliniagarwal

4. The fabulous Prabhat Choudhary, founder of @spicesocial, who is the film industry's image maker (and such an interesting man to talk with about branding, fame, and what true influence means).

5. With my partner-in-table-seating: the utterly wonderful @mehernaazdhondy , from Grazia India

6. The mandatory mirror selfie. Notice the blue lining on the border, which adds such a delicious touch when you move

7. The handbag that looks like a giveaway bag. Someone asked me where I got the goodie bag from!

8. The designers who have shaped the Indian Fashion scene, made it what it is today, and brought pride to so many of us.

9. And finally, the incomparable @kareenakapoorkhan . Still the blueprint. Still the baddest. Still Bebo.

10. Bye.

#LakmeFashionWeek #FDCI

latestPosts.caption:
The Word. Costume for a Cause Gala...13.04.2025.

Editor-in-Chief: Nandini Bhalla (@nandinibhalla)
Styling: Faris Ansari (@tofu_curryy)
Creative Direction: (@the_social_solution)
Muse: Lakshmi Rana (@lakshmirana)
Videographer: @stellariosart
Make-up: Harshita Joshi (@hersheymakeup) 
Hair: Adil Khan (@hairbyadilkhan )

 

Lakshmi is wearing a gown and headpiece by Rahul Mishra (@rahulmishra_7 ). And gloves by Outhouse (@outhousejewellery)

#TheWordGala #CostumeforaCause #Mumbai

Are women bad at accepting compliments?
This was one of the discussions we had at the special The Word. Magazine X Bobbi Brown lunch, held in Mumbai.

There are gatherings, and then there are gatherings that feel like a soothing hug, with the warmth of sisterhood and genuine connection. This was the latter, as friends of The Word. gathered to share personal experiences and stories about life, confidence, and what brings out their 'inner glow'.

The conversations around the table were raw, honest...and emotional.

Actor and Bobbi Brown India brand ambassador @tarasutaria talked about what self-love, confidence, and authenticity mean to her, and other guests shared personal anecdotes about self acceptance and why women struggle to accept compliments (just take that compliment and say thank you!).

We got to sample and slather on Bobbi Brown's fabulous Vitamin Enriched range, which is packed with skin-loving nutrients for a luminous glow. Followed by a relaxing sound-healing session, which centred our souls. 

As the lunch concluded,  we left with more than just goody bags holding Bobbi Brown products...we carried with us a renewed sense of self and an inner glow that lasted for days.

Community Partner: Soho House, Mumbai (@sohohouse)

#TheWordMagazine #TheWordXBobbiBrown #BobbiBrownIndia #MyDailyGlow

latestPosts.caption:
I have to say, the @fdciofficial Men's Fashion Week 2025 was an incredible experience.  An intimate gathering in Jaipur, featuring a careful selection of India's finest menswear designers!

Over 2 days, we watched classic tradition collide with radical reinvention. Contemporary masculinity was at the forefront, as whimsical prints, skirts, jewellery, and gender-fluid silhouettes made appearances.

Detailed stories coming up on @thewordmagazine , but in the meantime, I'll give you a hint: the boys of 2025 aren't here to follow your rules!

I'm wearing an unapologetic riot of colours by @bansal.siddhartha
And a very interesting bustier by a cool, new label called @onetruepairing.in
And a @cord.in set that is the perfect example of how you'll wear something over and over when you love it!

#MensFashionWeek #FDCI #ChivasLuxeCollective

Last night, celebrating the magic of Sabyasachi over 
25 years. 

Journalists, clients, muses, and friends came together for a show that was a grand homage to the talent, vision, and craft-centred skill of Sabyasachi Mukherjee...the man who has inspired generations and redefined Indian luxury for a global stage.

Take a bow, Sabya. Take 10. Your legacy is a masterpiece, shining bright.

PS: I'm wearing a beautifully crafted jacket by designer @minisondhiofficial ♥️
